
Overview of noun confirmation

The noun confirmation has 5 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                   
1. (4) confirmation, verification, check, substantiation -- (additional proof that something that was believed (some fact or hypothesis or theory) is correct; "fossils provided further confirmation of the evolutionary theory")
2. (1) confirmation -- (information that confirms or verifies)
3. ratification, confirmation -- (making something valid by formally ratifying or confirming it; "the ratification of the treaty"; "confirmation of the appointment")
4. confirmation -- (a ceremony held in the synagogue (usually at Pentecost) to admit as adult members of the Jewish community young men and women who have successfully completed a course of study in Judaism)
5. confirmation -- (a sacrament admitting a baptized person to full participation in the church)
